SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 61
By Walley
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Billy Ray Helton, Sr., of
Lawrenceburg.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Billy Ray Helton, Sr.; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Helton was an exemplary public servant and consummate professional
who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow citizens in numerous
capacities; and
WHEREAS, a native of Lawrenceburg, Mr. Helton served with acumen and alacrity as
the president and chief executive officer of Lawrenceburg Federal Bank for a number of years;
and
WHEREAS, in addition to his career in banking, he served as a trustee for Freed-
Hardeman University, commissioner of finance for Lawrenceburg, and vice mayor of
Lawrenceburg; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Helton was an active and devout member of the Pulaski Street Church
of Christ, which he served faithfully for many years as an elder, deacon, and teacher; and
WHEREAS, deeply devoted to his family, Mr. Helton always endeavored to remain true
to family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, Billy Helton enjoyed the loving companionship of his wife, Donna G. Abrams
Helton, who preceded him in death; he was the proud father of Billy R. "Biff" (Penny) Helton, Jr.,
Angie (Terry) Wright, Andrea Helton, and Holly (Daniel) Winkler; and
WHEREAS, he is further survived by his eleven grandchildren and fourteen great-
grandchildren; and
WHEREAS, in addition to his wife, Mr. Helton was preceded in death by his parents,
William and Edna Jackson Helton, and two siblings, Gene Helton and Betty Brewer; and
